To install `@ts-migrating`, run `npm install -D ts-migrating`. Then, add it as a plugin in your `tsconfig.json`:


{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "plugins": [
      {
        "name": "ts-migrating",
        "compilerOptions": {
          "noUncheckedIndexedAccess": true
        }
      }
    ]
  }
}

This enables the plugin for IDE support (e.g., VS Code) but does not affect `tsc` or production builds.

Here’s an example function where `@ts-migrating` temporarily suppresses the error from `noUncheckedIndexedAccess: true`:

ts
function first(xs: number[]): number {
  // @ts-migrating
  return xs[0]; // Error is suppressed for this line only
}

The `// @ts-migrating` comment marks the line as intentionally falling back to the old behavior, allowing the team to address it later without hiding unrelated bugs.
